results.name: Number of ways a loop can cross three roads meeting in a Y n times.
comment: The Mercedes-Benz problem: closed meanders crossing a Y.
example: With three crossings the loop must cut each road exactly once, so a(3) = 1.
xref: Similar to A078104, but without the constraint of touching the (-, -) quadrant.
results.author: _N. J. A. Sloane_ and _Jon Wild_, Aug 25 2003
